      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Your frustration highlights the profound emotional weight of humanity's insignificance, but the James Webb observations actually reveal galaxies forming just as the universe began, suggesting a deep, ancient history rather than empty voids. The sensation that these efforts are in vain is a powerful existential thought that has driven science since humanity first gazed upward, proving that meaning is often found in the connection of our curiosity rather than in an ending of the story. It is a painful reminder to cherish every fleeting moment of discovery because the universe itself persists in a grand, indifferent dance that makes human wonder particularly precious.",
